    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>French 18th-century term for small tiered tables, usually of tripod form, with movable arms to support candlesticks; generally used by women both for work and for reading.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Término francés del siglo XVIII para mesas pequeñas con gradas, normalmente con forma de trípode, con brazos móviles para apoyar candelabros; generalmente empleados por mujeres para trabajar y leer.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Franse benaming uit de 18e eeuw voor kleine, gelaagde tafeltjes, meestal met drie poten en beweegbare steuntjes voor kaarsen. Ze werden meestal gebruikt door vrouwen om aan te werken of te lezen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>十八世紀法國的詞彙，指一種小型的層疊檯桌，通常為三隻桌腳的形式，有放置燭臺的可動式扶手，一般為女性工作或閱讀時使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
